                "href": "/profile/Chris-Tion-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Everybody is not inherently racist. That\u2019s the same ignorant and simple thinking that leads to being racist in the first place. There are 7 billion people on this rock. And to have the arrogance to speak for all 7 billion about racism is quite telling. We know for a fact you probably couldn\u2019t name a specific characteristic for all 196 countries, but you think you can tell something about all 7 billion people. You must be like Professor Charles Xavier from the X-Men. Now me personally, as a black man in America, grew up with white family my entire life. That\u2019s right. White people loved me before I found out that there were white people that hated me just for being black so I was easily able to differentiate. I\u2019ve never been racist. I\u2019ve always judged everybody as individuals. Considering that there are actually biracial people, the ideology of everybody being racist should immediately explode from your head. One of my favorite cousin\u2019s is biracial. Just because you\u2019re racist, don\u2019t try to justify it by painting your weakness on the whole world. If you choose to ignore that racism is strictly a social concept and has no truth in biology, that\u2019s your ignorance shining and I\u2019d appreciate it if you keep it to yourself. ",
