                "name": "Bala Senthil Kumar",
                "href": "/profile/Bala-Senthil-Kumar"
            },
            "answer_text": "Not just racism but being discriminatory is easily learned. Very few of us humans are brought up to love and embrace without fear or suspicion of another - whatever that may be. Very few of us can be accepting of things that we are conditioned to recognize as \"not so good\". It is easy to be kind and loving when we are in environments where there is no threat to any of our belief systems.  Take people out of this comfort zone and you will see their real natures coming out. For example, I know people who are into meditation and yoga and healthy living and that sort of thing, and choose to insulate themselves from the outside world as they see it.  Meet them in their domain and they will be the nicest, kindest, most wonderful, smiling people.  Put some of them in a bus in downtown Los Angeles, and you can see them being repulsed! To me, a cool person is who can be comfortable flying a private plane, sharing a sandwich and a conversation with a homeless person, be generous and grin even when all is lost!  Very few parents know how to raise a kid to become something like this. ",
